{
  "texts": [
    "Guided by the relatively large amplitude of the detected signal and by theoretical and observational advancements in the last decade, we select a sub-sample of those models, as we now justify.",
    "First, hydrodynamical simulations of merging galaxies at different scales as well as deep X-ray observations of merging galaxies support accretion activation onto the individual SMBHs prior to merger (e.g.",
    "Capelo et al. 2017; Koss et al. 2018).",
    "Moreover, hydrodynamical simulations of sub-pc scale binaries, have found most of the accretion to occur on the secondary (i.e.",
    "less massive) SMBH (Farris et al. 2014)."
  ]
}